row.question: At a company meeting, M men and W women meet in a conference room. If the ratio of men to women is 2:3 at the meeting and the conference room can hold no more than 64 people, then what is the maximum number of women who can be at the meeting?
row.rationale:
M=2W/3
W+M=5W/3 <= 64
W <= 38.4
If W=38, then M=25.3 (inadmissible)
If W=37, then M=24.7 (inadmissible)
Then W = 36 and M = 24.
The answer is B.
